data modify block ~ ~ ~ Book set value {components:{"minecraft:writable_book_content":{pages:[{raw:"/Thank you for your purchase of a 2026 TERFTECH™ Redstone Sequencer!\n\nHere are some examples to give you an insight of it's programming language.\n\nSlashes mark the starts and stops of comments like the one you're looking at now."},{raw:"A list of instructions:\n\n+; turns on all bulbs\n-; turns off all bulbs\n\n+1; turns on the bulb with the address of 1\n\n-1; turns off the bulb with the address of 1\n\nw; pause for 1 tick\nw9; pause for 9 ticks"},{raw:'l5[] loops the instructions in the brackets 5 times\n\nIf your program errors out, you can use a multimeter on the lectern to get the error message which usually shows the page number as "Pg" and the character (from last to first) as "Char"'},{raw:'The compiler ignores all characters that are not "+-wl]" or a slash, meaning you can indent your code like:\n\nl10[\n +1; w10; -1; w10;\n]'},{raw:"anyways, if you connect 3 bulbs to 3 note blocks with their note values being 3, 5 and 7 you can listen to the built in music program below:/\n\n-; w5;\n+3; w5; -;\n+2; w5; -;\n+1; w5; -;\n+2; w5; -;\nl3[+3; w3; -; w2;] w5;"},{raw:"l3[+2; w3; -; w2;] w5;\n+1; w5; -;\nl2[+3; w3; -; w2;] w5;\n+3; w5; -;\n+2; w5; -;\n+1; w5; -;\n+2; w5; -;\nl4[+3; w3; -; w2;];\nl2[+2; w3; -; w2;];\n+3; w5; -;\n+2; w5; -;\n+1; w5; -;\nw10; l3[+; w2; -; w2;]"},{raw:"/This will run too many instructions in 1 tick crashing the program for showcase/\n\nl69[+; -;]"}]}},count:1,id:"minecraft:writable_book"}